  "prompt": "Is it possible to change names in savings a/c?",
  "response": "Yes, it is generally possible to change the name on a savings account, but the exact process can vary depending on the bank and their policies. Here are the common steps you might need to follow:\n\n1. **Contact the Bank**: Reach out to your bank\u2019s customer service or visit a branch. Explain that you want to change the name on your account.\n\n2. **Provide Documentation**: You will likely need to provide legal documentation to support the name change. This might include:\n   - A marriage certificate (if changing due to marriage)\n   - A divorce decree (if reverting to a maiden name)\n   - A court order\n   - A government-issued ID with the new name\n\n3. **Complete Forms**: The bank may require you to fill out a name change form or application.\n\n4. **Identity Verification**: Be prepared to verify your identity, which may involve presenting additional identification.\n\n5. **Waiting Period**: After submitting your request and documentation, there might be a waiting period before the name change is officially processed.\n\n6. **Confirmation**: Once the name change is completed, you should receive confirmation from the bank. Be sure to check your account details to ensure everything is accurate.\n\nAlways check with your specific bank for their requirements and procedures, as they can differ.",
